18
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:25,580
 There's no sound in the world I live in. 

19
00:01:25,580 --> 00:01:30,180
 So if I close my eyes, the world disappears. 

20
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:35,190
 Instead, I only remember this very old memory vividly. 

21
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:41,190
 Someone's hands that called my name instead of their voice. 

22
00:01:41,190 --> 00:01:44,750
 Cheong Ah. 

23
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,570
 Clear. 

24
00:01:54,930 --> 00:01:56,600
 Sound. 

25
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:20,410
 Mom. 

26
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,460
 I like you. 

27
00:02:36,550 --> 00:02:38,460
 I love you. 

28
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:40,770
 I had a name then. 

29
00:02:40,770 --> 00:02:43,050
 I could smile, too. 

30
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:44,720
 But... 

31
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:53,800
 Cheong Ah. Cheong Ah. 

32
00:02:59,410 --> 00:03:02,640
   

33
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:05,500
   

34
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:08,770
 Cheong Ah! 

35
00:03:57,790 --> 00:04:00,210
 You're Cheong Ah. 

36
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:06,560
 I'm the resident teacher who will educate you starting today. 

37
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:09,220
 That damn evil lady. 

38
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:11,200
 A witch who came to ruin my life. 

39
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,610
 Pa. 

40
00:04:14,550 --> 00:04:16,350
 Pa. 

41
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:44,490
 Pa! 

42
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:39,510
 All I had left was anger then. 

43
00:05:45,490 --> 00:05:50,360
 Because I lost the language to express myself and my feelings. 

44
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:12,480
 Hello. 

45
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:17,880
 So embarrassing! I'm so embarrassed! 

46
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:38,060
 - Hey! 
 - Gosh, I'm sorry. 

47
00:06:52,530 --> 00:06:58,180
 The day I first saw you, I was able to laugh my heart out. 

48
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:23,550
 The day I saw you for the second time, 

49
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:26,970
 I felt my heart beating for the first time. 

50
00:07:26,970 --> 00:07:30,210
 I'm giving you this free of charge. 

51
00:07:30,210 --> 00:07:31,790
 Thank you. 

52
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,080
 You got three vanillas, right? 

53
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:35,300
 Starting from the third time, I went to see you myself. 

54
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:37,870
 Really? You have a beautiful heart, too. 

55
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:39,050
 My heart is also... 

56
00:07:39,050 --> 00:07:41,210
 I'm sure you didn't notice. 

57
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,410
 Have a good day. 

58
00:07:42,410 --> 00:07:44,050
 Bye. 

59
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:02,090
 I also... 

60
00:08:02,890 --> 00:08:04,520
 am in a band! 

61
00:08:07,410 --> 00:08:08,900
 Choi Se Kyeong. 

62
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:11,630
 Want to come to my band's concert later? 

63
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:14,990
 If I didn't lend Se Kyeong that T-shirt... 

64
00:08:14,990 --> 00:08:17,040
 My school is having a festival in a month. 

65
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:19,920
 I'll prepare a performance just for you. Make sure to come. 

66
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:24,310
 ...would I be standing in front of you now? 

67
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:28,140
 I closed my eyes again. 

68
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:31,300
 Because I wanted the world to disappear. 

69
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:02,210
 But... 

70
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:09,330
 you somehow always show up whenever I'm trapped somewhere. 

71
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:15,210
 I'm sorry I bit your hand. 

72
00:09:17,770 --> 00:09:20,200
 I'm sorry I was mean to you. 

73
00:09:25,050 --> 00:09:27,450
 Send me an SOS if you need help. 

74
00:09:27,450 --> 00:09:30,740
 I'm out now, then. 

75
00:09:44,270 --> 00:09:48,200
   

76
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,820
 I didn't do that because I hated you. 

77
00:09:50,820 --> 00:09:52,740
 To be honest... 

78
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:01,550
 I wanted to say thank you. 

79
00:10:05,770 --> 00:10:10,500
 I wanted to thank you for helping and discovering me. 

80
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,450
 That's why I went to see you. 

81
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:16,760
 I wanted to express how I feel somehow. But... 

82
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:27,420
Se Kyeong.

83
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:31,160
Hi. Long time no see, Lee Chan.

84
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,800
 But... 

85
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:40,540
 I think I'm too late this time, too. 

86
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:45,380
   

87
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:03,580
Wait, Se Kyeong. Wait just a moment. Wait.

88
00:11:10,070 --> 00:11:11,980
What's with you?

89
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:16,200
I don't know what you're asking because your question is too short.

90
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:20,810
You said you came back to die.

91
00:11:20,810 --> 00:11:23,310
You said you were still deciding if you should die or not.

92
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:25,720
You told me not to tell anyone unless I want to die.

93
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:28,280
You disappeared after threatening me like that.

94
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:31,100
What's the reason you showed up here yourself?

95
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:32,960
Oh, my goodness.

96
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,900
The question was that long?

97
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:37,820
Of course. I'm not bad at understanding—

98
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:40,510
Stop changing the subject and answer.

99
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:45,840
It's because of you.

100
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,990
What?

101
00:11:46,990 --> 00:11:49,840
Why are you pretending you didn't hear me? You did.

102
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:52,310
Because of you, I said.

103
00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:05,250
Hey. Hey!

104
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,690
Hold on.

105
00:12:06,690 --> 00:12:08,990
Right. She can't hear me.

106
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:20,530
I didn't do it.

107
00:12:20,530 --> 00:12:22,680
I, um...

108
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:26,780
Hold on.

109
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:48,040
   

110
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:56,060
Because of me?

111
00:12:56,060 --> 00:12:58,590
What do you mean?

112
00:12:58,590 --> 00:13:00,390
It stopped raining.

113
00:13:00,390 --> 00:13:02,550
Answer me. I asked you, what do you mean?

114
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:05,220
You scared me. Why are you yelling at me?

115
00:13:05,220 --> 00:13:08,300
You told me I wasn't supposed to return.

116
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:13,150
I was curious what would happen if I didn't listen to you, so I came back. Happy?

117
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:15,920
Do you look down on Lee Chan that much?

118
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:18,920
You're not just jumping to conclusion. You're provoking me.

119
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:20,500
When did I say I look down on him?

120
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:25,240
You're saying you'd toy with his heart out of curiosity right now.

121
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,420
You said you wanted to die. But you want to have fun, too?

122
00:13:27,420 --> 00:13:29,420
Am I not supposed to have fun?

123
00:13:29,420 --> 00:13:31,080
- What? 
 - Or...

124
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,780
are you telling me to decide quickly if I'll die or not?

125
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:35,030
- That's not what I'm saying— 
 - If not,

126
00:13:35,030 --> 00:13:39,050
are you telling me to shut up and die quietly since I'll die anyway?

127
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:41,350
Don't worry.

128
00:13:41,350 --> 00:13:44,600
I'll disappear for you when the time comes.

129
00:13:45,370 --> 00:13:48,920
Are you really the Choi Se Kyeong I know?

130
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:52,740
 Se Kyeong! Choi Se Kyeong! 

131
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:56,020
I am Choi Se Kyeong according to him.

132
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,270
I'm sorry. I made you wait too long.

133
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:03,880
Not at all. I'm sorry I showed up without notice.

134
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:07,860
Lee Chan, can we talk for a second?

135
00:14:07,860 --> 00:14:12,630
I-I'll tell the manager real quick and come back.

136
00:14:13,910 --> 00:14:15,770
Sir.

137
00:14:16,470 --> 00:14:18,430
Aren't you leaving?

138
00:14:18,430 --> 00:14:22,180
You won't be childish and butt in or anything. Right?

139
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:36,480
I heard you left to study abroad. What brings you here...

140
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:43,690
Do I...

141
00:14:43,690 --> 00:14:47,420
So this is what you looked like, Lee Chan.

142
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:50,420
You're way more handsome than I thought.

143
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:53,660
A-Are you here to mock me?

144
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:58,190
No way. The flight is too expensive for that.

145
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:01,010
I just had a bit of a situation.

146
00:15:01,010 --> 00:15:02,640
What situation?

147
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:04,390
It seems like no one knows you're back.

148
00:15:04,390 --> 00:15:07,330
Of course not. I came back yesterday.

149
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:11,430
So far, only you know that I'm back.

150
00:15:13,730 --> 00:15:16,830
Are you back for good?

151
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:21,290
I don't know. I'm still deciding that.

152
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:23,310
Why did you come to see me then?

153
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:26,200
You left without saying a word before.

154
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,390
I wanted to apologize.

155
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:33,980
I feel guilty that I've been rude to you.

156
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:38,020
I'm sorry I looked down on you even though I didn't know much about you.

157
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,790
I apologize.

158
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:41,790
And...

159
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:44,470
I'd like to learn about you from now on.

160
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:48,520
Of course, I'll take the bet seriously, too.

161
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:56,490
Seriously, why isn't he coming?

162
00:16:00,850 --> 00:16:03,030
What did she say? Why did she come?

163
00:16:03,030 --> 00:16:05,690
Why did she come to see you, anyway?

164
00:16:05,690 --> 00:16:07,440
Have you...

165
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:10,000
been in a relationship?

166
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,550
- A relationship? 
 - Yes.

167
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,990
Well...

168
00:16:14,990 --> 00:16:17,000
of course...

169
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:20,650
It's okay. I already got your answer.

170
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:23,400
Your eyes were shaking like crazy.

171
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,300
Poor bastard.

172
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,320
You're a fool who doesn't even know what love is.

173
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:34,390
You've never been in a relationship. How could you understand

174
00:16:34,390 --> 00:16:38,000
the complex conversation I had with Se Kyeong.

175
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,520
- So she told me— 
 - Forget it.

176
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:42,260
I'm not curious at all.

177
00:16:42,260 --> 00:16:43,960
Try saying another word.

178
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:46,260
Hey, boy. Ask me politely one more time.

179
00:16:46,260 --> 00:16:48,050
I might give you the answer.

180
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:50,730
I know you're actually curious. Okay? Come on.

181
00:16:50,730 --> 00:16:52,770
   

182
00:17:01,620 --> 00:17:03,480
I'm not interested.

183
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:05,810
I'm not interested at all.

184
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:12,570
 Ha Lee Chan! 

185
00:17:12,570 --> 00:17:18,170
Se Kyeong was standing in front of me with her new haircut.

186
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:21,150
My heart started getting excited first.

187
00:17:21,150 --> 00:17:23,670
I'm serious. I'm serious. I'm serious.

188
00:17:23,670 --> 00:17:26,120
What else can I do? I had to fall in love again.

189
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:29,090
Hey, hey, hey. So, who does she look like again?

190
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:30,530
Lee Young Ae?

191
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:33,520
She used to. Now she looks like Ko So Young.

192
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:37,520
She used to seep in subtly like an electrolyte drink before.

193
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:40,250
But now she's like...

194
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:44,190
a soda that shocks you from within.

195
00:17:44,190 --> 00:17:47,850
What a crazy analogy. Seriously.

196
00:17:47,850 --> 00:17:49,910
Come close.

197
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:52,580
How could I hold onto Se Kyeong more securely?

198
00:17:52,580 --> 00:17:55,690
Hey, you already have her.

199
00:17:55,690 --> 00:17:58,820
- Really? 
 - Listen carefully.

200
00:17:58,820 --> 00:18:03,130
Women have veins in their hair.

201
00:18:03,130 --> 00:18:05,130
Blood runs through it.

202
00:18:05,130 --> 00:18:07,790
But she cut it short?

203
00:18:07,790 --> 00:18:10,190
It means she cut off her veins.

204
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:12,690
She's crying bloody tears.

205
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:14,480
Why? Why? Why? Why? Why?

206
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,570
What do you mean, why? Because of you!

207
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:18,590
My gosh.

208
00:18:19,860 --> 00:18:22,350
- Because of me? 
 - You said she showed up on her own.

209
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:26,190
- Yes. 
 - And she apologized for being rude.

210
00:18:26,190 --> 00:18:28,220
She said she wants to get to know you

211
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:31,150
and she'll take the bet seriously, too. What does that all mean?

212
00:18:31,150 --> 00:18:34,520
I don't know. What does it mean?

213
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:37,530
She realized how precious you are after leaving.

214
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:39,330
She regretted that she let go of you.

215
00:18:39,330 --> 00:18:41,690
She cried bloody tears, regretting.

216
00:18:41,690 --> 00:18:44,030
And she suddenly finds you handsome?

217
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:46,180
She was blinded by love. That's it.

218
00:18:46,180 --> 00:18:49,190
- That's it. 
 - Game over.

219
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:52,320
What do I do, guys?

220
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:55,470
I can't handle my charm anymore, either.

221
00:18:56,730 --> 00:18:59,740
 Hey, hey, hey! Ha Lee Chan! 

222
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:02,350
 Ha Lee Chan! 

223
00:19:08,690 --> 00:19:13,560
He really came up with a line straight out of a trot song?

224
00:19:22,890 --> 00:19:24,300
When she was like that?

225
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:27,580
 Open it. He left this to you. 

226
00:19:27,580 --> 00:19:30,480
But that's how Ahjumma was.

227
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:32,930
Are they really the same person?

228
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:34,830
What was she thinking...

229
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:36,760
 I came to die. 

230
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:38,450
 To die. 

231
00:19:38,450 --> 00:19:40,340
 To end everything. 

232
00:19:40,340 --> 00:19:41,760
 Don't worry. 

233
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:44,750
 I'll disappear for you when the time comes. 

234
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,800
She can't...

235
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:50,420
actually be thinking of dying. Right?

236
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,460
Hey.

237
00:20:01,460 --> 00:20:03,860
What are you doing here?

238
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:07,880
How did you know where I live?

239
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:11,730
I've been here with Lee Chan before.

240
00:20:11,730 --> 00:20:14,010
Don't you remember?

241
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:18,180
Did you?

242
00:20:18,180 --> 00:20:22,750
Lee Chan really is worse than dirt under your toenail.

243
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:26,250
Whatever. I asked you why you came here.

244
00:20:28,410 --> 00:20:32,380
Forget it. I guess you won't die for a while.

245
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:36,020
Are you here because you were worried about me?

246
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:39,610
You're more angelic than I thought.

247
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:52,270
If you threaten people as a hobby, you'll grow up to be a scammer.

248
00:20:52,270 --> 00:20:55,280
You have a lot of potential. So watch out from now on.

249
00:20:55,990 --> 00:20:58,100
You seem to have a lot of potential, too.

250
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:59,700
Is that so?

251
00:21:02,470 --> 00:21:04,710
Should I try using it more?

252
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:08,810
Don't show up in front of Lee Chan ever again.

253
00:21:08,810 --> 00:21:10,900
This is my final warning.

254
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:45,250
   

255
00:21:46,610 --> 00:21:48,680
Hey, where do you think you're going?

256
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,330
I'll borrow it for a second. I'm sorry!

257
00:21:50,330 --> 00:21:54,340
Is he out of his mind? Hey, stop! That's my skateboard!

258
00:21:59,950 --> 00:22:03,120
Move! Out of the way!

259
00:22:21,350 --> 00:22:25,950
   

260
00:22:54,670 --> 00:22:56,580
Welcome, Frontman.

261
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:58,410
We've been waiting for you.

262
00:22:58,410 --> 00:23:00,520
Are you ready to enjoy our first practice together?

263
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,140
You're ready to burn the stage down. Right?

264
00:23:02,140 --> 00:23:03,910
Everybody, make some noise.

265
00:23:03,910 --> 00:23:07,870
 We are ready! 

266
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,930
Come on, brothers.

267
00:23:17,820 --> 00:23:20,360
You're out of your mind. You're late to our first practice?

268
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:21,730
Did you ride the skateboard here, by chance?

