528
00:38:09,220 --> 00:38:11,620
But you're saying it's not Lee Chan.

529
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:14,000
That means you like me, then.

530
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:16,990
This is when you say, "Out of the frying pan into the fire," right?

531
00:38:16,990 --> 00:38:18,840
Goodbye.

532
00:38:21,950 --> 00:38:24,350
Just be honest.

533
00:38:26,020 --> 00:38:31,070
Is it me or Lee Chan?

534
00:38:47,860 --> 00:38:52,170
D-Don't be mistaken and think everyone in the world likes you.

535
00:38:52,170 --> 00:38:53,810
I'm not mistaken.

536
00:38:53,810 --> 00:38:56,230
Everyone likes me.

537
00:38:58,450 --> 00:39:01,030
I'm sorry, but you're not my type.

538
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:07,250
That punk. It's so fun to tease him.

539
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:15,670
Get it together.

540
00:39:16,430 --> 00:39:19,500
Please, get it together.

541
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:20,760
Please!

542
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:22,540
You scared me!

543
00:39:22,540 --> 00:39:25,770
I'm worried about Se Kyeong because she is alone.

544
00:39:25,770 --> 00:39:27,190
G-Give me your pager.

545
00:39:27,190 --> 00:39:30,160
I-I'm confiscating it until the tutoring ends.

546
00:39:30,890 --> 00:39:32,540
My gosh.

547
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:35,510
There's Se Kyeong.

548
00:39:35,510 --> 00:39:37,350
Se Kyeong.

549
00:39:41,570 --> 00:39:43,530
Se Kyeong.

550
00:39:44,410 --> 00:39:46,550
Is this your home phone number?

551
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:49,020
I'll save it in my heart.

552
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:54,300
No. I'm just happy you got home safely.

553
00:39:54,300 --> 00:39:56,190
Hang up while I'm asking you nicely.

554
00:39:56,190 --> 00:39:57,870
The tutoring session hasn't ended yet.

555
00:39:57,870 --> 00:39:59,520
Huh?

556
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:00,750
That noise just now?

557
00:40:00,750 --> 00:40:03,720
It's nothing. A fly is buzzing around.

558
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:06,040
Fly? Give it to me.

559
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:08,050
- Give me! 
 - Se Kyeong.

560
00:40:08,050 --> 00:40:10,520
I'll go kill that fly.

561
00:40:17,060 --> 00:40:20,270
Se Kyeong, I killed it. Sorry for making you wait.

562
00:40:20,270 --> 00:40:23,190
Even my dad never hit me. Come here!

563
00:40:23,190 --> 00:40:25,340
Come here.

564
00:40:25,340 --> 00:40:28,030
There are more bugs than I thought.

565
00:40:29,500 --> 00:40:31,930
I'll kill it real quick...

566
00:40:34,840 --> 00:40:37,620
Don't call me a bug! Give it!

567
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:42,780
I killed it. I killed it.

568
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:47,000
You want to change the final song? What do you mean?

569
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:50,580
The final song is your mission song, too. Would that be okay?

570
00:40:50,580 --> 00:40:52,100
Of course, it's okay.

571
00:40:52,100 --> 00:40:53,990
Se Kyeong told me to change it.

572
00:40:53,990 --> 00:40:55,590
Why all of a sudden?

573
00:40:55,590 --> 00:40:59,390
To be honest, I asked her on the phone last night.

574
00:40:59,390 --> 00:41:03,370
I asked her if she was really trying to sabotage me with that song.

575
00:41:04,100 --> 00:41:05,710
I said that's what you guys think.

576
00:41:05,710 --> 00:41:07,300
And?

577
00:41:08,060 --> 00:41:09,680
 Change it, then. 

578
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:12,290
 You don't have to play American pop songs only because you're a band. 

579
00:41:12,290 --> 00:41:17,800
 Korean pop might dominate the Billboard charts and enter the global market someday. 

580
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:20,310
 You should be leading trends, too. 

581
00:41:20,310 --> 00:41:23,410
Wow, she thinks big now that she's been to the US.

582
00:41:23,410 --> 00:41:25,240
I'm on board. I'm definitely on board.

583
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:28,700
Me, too. That song would've been too hard for us anyway.

584
00:41:28,700 --> 00:41:31,210
I'm on board, too, then.

585
00:41:31,210 --> 00:41:33,200
I'm against it.

586
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:36,510
What are you all doing right now?

587
00:41:36,510 --> 00:41:38,170
The festival is less than a month away.

588
00:41:38,170 --> 00:41:41,540
I would've been against it even if we had plenty of time.

589
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:43,810
We're changing the song just because of what she said?

590
00:41:43,810 --> 00:41:46,380
Why not? The one who's betting wants me to change it.

591
00:41:46,380 --> 00:41:48,200
What if she changes her mind?

592
00:41:48,200 --> 00:41:51,100
- We'll make changes based on her whims? 
 - Of course.

593
00:41:51,100 --> 00:41:54,150
She gave up on her studies abroad and came back for me.

594
00:41:54,150 --> 00:41:56,790
I'll do whatever she wants me to do.

595
00:41:56,790 --> 00:41:58,740
I'll keep my promise to her with my life on the line.

596
00:41:58,740 --> 00:42:00,490
Is your promise to me in the trash, then?

597
00:42:00,490 --> 00:42:02,250
Gosh, you scared me.

598
00:42:02,250 --> 00:42:05,550
What promise did I make to you?

599
00:42:08,110 --> 00:42:10,000
Okay.

600
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:12,870
I'll leave, then.

601
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:15,550
I can just do that.

602
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:18,350
Hey, hey, hey.

603
00:42:18,350 --> 00:42:21,560
Wow, he's acting superior because he's a good guitarist.

604
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:25,540
If the word "petty" took on a human form, it'd look like him.

605
00:42:25,540 --> 00:42:28,320
What are you doing? Go follow him.

606
00:42:28,320 --> 00:42:30,760
Go to him right now.

607
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:32,910
Stop right there while I'm asking nicely.

608
00:42:32,910 --> 00:42:35,820
Hey! Seriously...

609
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:38,820
The mood got ruined because of you.

610
00:42:38,820 --> 00:42:40,960
Everyone's happy about it. Why are you flipping out?

611
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:42,920
Is the band a joke to you?

612
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:45,220
Is it just for seducing a woman?

613
00:42:45,220 --> 00:42:46,920
Someone...

614
00:42:47,620 --> 00:42:50,420
broke his parents' hearts because he wanted to join a band.

615
00:42:50,420 --> 00:42:51,670
Dang it...

616
00:42:51,670 --> 00:42:55,930
We're just changing a song. Why bring up breaking parents' hearts?

617
00:42:55,930 --> 00:42:59,660
You let her sweet talk you and fiddle around like a fiddle stick.

618
00:42:59,660 --> 00:43:01,920
You don't even remember our promise, do you?

619
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:05,470
You don't care if other people get hurt except Choi Se Kyeong. Right?

620
00:43:05,470 --> 00:43:10,310
Whatever. Just tell me. Will you stay in the band or not?

621
00:43:11,970 --> 00:43:13,610
Okay.

622
00:43:13,610 --> 00:43:15,470
Let's forget it.

623
00:43:15,470 --> 00:43:17,600
I'm getting tired now, too.

624
00:43:18,670 --> 00:43:22,100
I shouldn't care what happens to you.

625
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:24,130
Let's just forget it.

626
00:43:24,910 --> 00:43:27,300
Don't do anything you'd regret.

627
00:43:27,300 --> 00:43:29,900
I won't take you back if you leave like this.

628
00:43:29,900 --> 00:43:33,140
That includes the band and the boarding house!

629
00:43:33,140 --> 00:43:36,260
Hey! You're rejected everywhere!

630
00:43:39,460 --> 00:43:41,430
Water and oil don't mix.

631
00:43:41,430 --> 00:43:42,880
You scared me.

632
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:45,580
What a greasy bastard. He never even dated anyone.

633
00:43:45,580 --> 00:43:48,070
He's going through late puberty now.

634
00:43:48,070 --> 00:43:49,750
Why are you alone? Where's Ha Eun Gyeol?

635
00:43:49,750 --> 00:43:51,810
Whatever. Let's just practice.

636
00:43:51,810 --> 00:43:54,310
He'll come back once his juvenile angst goes away.

637
00:43:54,310 --> 00:43:58,750
He must think that, but no way. I'll never go back.

638
00:43:58,750 --> 00:44:00,920
   

639
00:44:00,920 --> 00:44:02,780
Young man.

640
00:44:02,780 --> 00:44:06,250
You're the good son who wanted to buy your father a guitar. Right?

641
00:44:06,250 --> 00:44:07,710
Hello.

642
00:44:07,710 --> 00:44:11,020
I got a guitar that meets your requirements perfectly.

643
00:44:11,020 --> 00:44:12,920
Have a look and take it if you like it.

644
00:44:12,920 --> 00:44:14,940
I'll sell it to you for whatever price you want.

645
00:44:14,940 --> 00:44:17,600
No, I don't need it anymore.

646
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:19,080
Well, then...

647
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:23,060
   

648
00:44:25,300 --> 00:44:27,030
He had a fight.

649
00:44:27,030 --> 00:44:29,710
He had a fight with his father.

650
00:44:30,890 --> 00:44:31,810
   

651
00:44:31,810 --> 00:44:37,440
   

652
00:44:56,060 --> 00:44:57,740
 Thank you. 

653
00:44:57,740 --> 00:45:01,440
 Get tasty food for yourself. 

654
00:45:02,060 --> 00:45:05,630
 I'm sorry I left without a word, Grandma. 

655
00:45:06,230 --> 00:45:08,210
 But... 

656
00:45:08,830 --> 00:45:11,180
 you know, Grandma... 

657
00:45:11,870 --> 00:45:15,850
 I just can't stand how immature Dad is. 

658
00:45:27,830 --> 00:45:30,110
I'm home.

659
00:45:35,640 --> 00:45:39,030
Why are you alone? Where's your tutor?

660
00:45:39,030 --> 00:45:40,830
That guy's not home yet?

661
00:45:40,830 --> 00:45:43,230
Listen to yourself! How rude!

662
00:45:43,230 --> 00:45:45,280
How dare you call your teacher "that guy"?

663
00:45:45,280 --> 00:45:47,490
Is your teacher the dog next door?

664
00:45:47,490 --> 00:45:49,630
You make me sad if you keep talking like that.

665
00:45:49,630 --> 00:45:52,260
People might think I'm the servant of this house

666
00:45:52,260 --> 00:45:54,910
and he's your grandson or something.

667
00:45:54,910 --> 00:45:57,180
So I'm asking why you're coming home alone.

668
00:45:57,180 --> 00:46:01,440
He went to school to see you earlier today. Didn't you see him?

669
00:46:02,480 --> 00:46:05,050
I did see him at school, but...

670
00:46:05,050 --> 00:46:08,170
He went to Chuncheon. He had business to attend to.

671
00:46:08,170 --> 00:46:10,620
I can put these in the drawer. Right?

672
00:46:10,620 --> 00:46:12,300
Make it tidy. Don't make a mess.

673
00:46:12,300 --> 00:46:13,310
Okay.

674
00:46:13,310 --> 00:46:14,840
Oh, right. Hey.

675
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:18,450
I found this while doing the laundry. Is this yours?

676
00:46:20,300 --> 00:46:22,510
Someone dropped it.

677
00:46:22,510 --> 00:46:24,910
You should give it back, then.

678
00:46:24,910 --> 00:46:27,730
You shouldn't have let it touch soapy water.

679
00:46:27,730 --> 00:46:31,420
It's fine. I can't even talk to her. It's a hassle.

680
00:46:31,420 --> 00:46:33,720
He's too young to be so lazy.

681
00:46:34,650 --> 00:46:38,020
I was thinking of roasting a chicken with ginseng.

682
00:46:38,020 --> 00:46:40,770
Is he coming back tomorrow?

683
00:46:49,070 --> 00:46:52,390
He's in the late stage of the Eight Grade Syndrome.

684
00:46:53,570 --> 00:46:55,980
You took your bag, too?

685
00:46:55,980 --> 00:46:58,230
Are you really angry?

686
00:46:58,230 --> 00:46:59,480
Do as you like.

687
00:46:59,480 --> 00:47:02,250
You're the one suffering for leaving home.

688
00:47:04,790 --> 00:47:07,390
It's nice to have the room to myself.

689
00:47:17,040 --> 00:47:22,460
 You don't care if other people get hurt except Choi Se Kyeong. Right? 

690
00:47:22,460 --> 00:47:24,280
How dare he act superior?

691
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:26,550
Just try coming back home.

692
00:47:28,710 --> 00:47:30,960
So spacious.

693
00:47:40,850 --> 00:47:44,410
Young man. Young man. Wake up.

694
00:47:44,410 --> 00:47:46,360
Young man!

695
00:47:49,880 --> 00:47:52,930
You can't sleep in front of a store like this.

696
00:47:55,540 --> 00:47:57,730
Did you run away from home by chance?

697
00:47:57,730 --> 00:47:59,890
Do I have to report you?

698
00:47:59,890 --> 00:48:01,580
No.

699
00:48:02,130 --> 00:48:04,710
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

700
00:48:04,710 --> 00:48:10,260
   

701
00:48:10,260 --> 00:48:15,490
   

702
00:48:26,350 --> 00:48:28,670
   
   

703
00:48:36,450 --> 00:48:37,650
Hello?

704
00:48:37,650 --> 00:48:40,730
 Bonsoir. 

705
00:48:42,580 --> 00:48:45,810
Did you figure out why you ended up there, sir?

706
00:48:45,810 --> 00:48:47,530
No.

707
00:48:47,530 --> 00:48:50,330
I don't care why. Everything is such a mess.

708
00:48:50,330 --> 00:48:52,960
Dad is smitten with his first love

709
00:48:52,960 --> 00:48:54,760
 and I have no idea where Mom is. 

710
00:48:54,760 --> 00:48:57,470
 People have a funny idea about me, and I had a huge fight with Dad. 

711
00:48:57,470 --> 00:48:59,220
Nothing seems to be working out.

712
00:48:59,220 --> 00:49:01,980
Goodness, oh, no, that's too bad.

713
00:49:03,270 --> 00:49:05,860
I don't care about the mission. I want to go home.

714
00:49:05,860 --> 00:49:10,030
I miss my real dad, not the immature Ha Lee Chan.

715
00:49:10,030 --> 00:49:11,570
 I miss Mom... 

716
00:49:11,570 --> 00:49:14,160
and Eun Ho, too.

717
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:19,050
So, please. Please. Please let me go home. Please?

718
00:49:19,050 --> 00:49:20,500
I don't know what to say.

719
00:49:20,500 --> 00:49:24,640
The portal for time travel won't open for a while.

720
00:49:24,640 --> 00:49:27,200
When does it open, then?

721
00:49:27,200 --> 00:49:29,810
- You'll find out in time— 
  - Will you really be like this? 

722
00:49:29,810 --> 00:49:31,650
You threw me back in the past without a plan.

723
00:49:31,650 --> 00:49:35,090
Will you keep acting irresponsibly like this?

724
00:49:35,090 --> 00:49:36,670
If you go back now,

725
00:49:36,670 --> 00:49:42,130
the year 2023 will be a lot different than when you left it.

726
00:49:42,130 --> 00:49:44,230
Do you still want to go back?

727
00:49:44,230 --> 00:49:46,140
What...

728
00:49:46,900 --> 00:49:47,900
are you talking about?

729
00:49:47,900 --> 00:49:50,940
Gosh, I guess you didn't know.

730
00:49:50,940 --> 00:49:56,890
Everything started changing the moment you arrived here.

731
00:50:00,500 --> 00:50:01,820
   

732
00:50:04,500 --> 00:50:06,910
 Wait! Excuse me. 

733
00:50:12,690 --> 00:50:14,530
   

734
00:50:14,530 --> 00:50:16,250
 Yoon Dong Jin? 

735
00:50:18,580 --> 00:50:20,770
 - It's you. 
 - No! It's true! 

736
00:50:22,610 --> 00:50:26,700
 It's true. I'm Yoon Dong Jin. 

737
00:50:26,700 --> 00:50:28,370
 I don't think so. 

738
00:50:28,370 --> 00:50:29,770
 What would make you believe me? 

739
00:50:29,770 --> 00:50:32,690
 The moment you played someone else's role, 

740
00:50:32,690 --> 00:50:36,430
 history has already started changing little by little. 

741
00:50:36,430 --> 00:50:41,280
 The fates of people you met probably changed as well. 

742
00:50:41,280 --> 00:50:44,400
 You told me I wasn't supposed to return. 

743
00:50:44,400 --> 00:50:48,220
 I was curious what would happen if I didn't listen to you, so I came back. Happy? 

744
00:50:48,220 --> 00:50:49,920
By chance...

745
00:50:51,470 --> 00:50:55,300
Dad's first love suddenly came back and

746
00:50:55,300 --> 00:50:59,020
the relationship that should've ended reconnected.

747
00:50:59,020 --> 00:51:01,870
Are those the variables that I caused?

748
00:51:01,870 --> 00:51:06,670
I'm not sure. A variable creates another variable, too. Yes.

749
00:51:06,670 --> 00:51:08,510
Stop pretending to be a shaman

750
00:51:08,510 --> 00:51:10,600
 and give me some kind of hint! 

751
00:51:10,600 --> 00:51:13,660
 A way to fix this situation, a way to prevent dad's accident, 

752
00:51:13,660 --> 00:51:15,380
or a way to find Mom.

753
00:51:15,380 --> 00:51:17,240
Give me something, please!

754
00:51:17,240 --> 00:51:20,530
Huh? I already gave you all the hints, then.

755
00:51:20,530 --> 00:51:21,800
What hints? What do you mean?

756
00:51:21,800 --> 00:51:26,230
Give it a thought. We'll talk again later.

757
00:51:28,650 --> 00:51:31,240
- Goodbye. 
 - Hold on. Hold on.

758
00:51:31,240 --> 00:51:34,020
Hello? Hello? Gosh...

759
00:51:45,900 --> 00:51:48,690
He gave me all the hints, then?

760
00:52:06,500 --> 00:52:10,420
Could it be this?

761
00:52:11,100 --> 00:52:13,070
   

762
00:52:13,070 --> 00:52:14,540
Hold on.

763
00:52:14,540 --> 00:52:17,130
 April 29th is... 

764
00:52:17,130 --> 00:52:19,130
 tomorrow. 

765
00:52:19,810 --> 00:52:23,220
 Can I find some kind of a clue if I go there? 

766
00:52:24,360 --> 00:52:27,180
Since it's the first electric guitar released by Jinsung Instruments,

767
00:52:27,180 --> 00:52:29,030
Father is very excited about it.

768
00:52:29,030 --> 00:52:32,100
Since I came here as Chairman's proxy,

769
00:52:32,100 --> 00:52:34,870
today's event has to be a success no matter what.

770
00:52:34,870 --> 00:52:37,490
Everything is going as planned. Right?

771
00:52:37,490 --> 00:52:41,520
Well, there's a bit of a problem.

772
00:52:41,520 --> 00:52:42,750
A problem?

773
00:52:42,750 --> 00:52:46,860
The weather forecast says there will be torrential rain with thunderstorms in the afternoon.

774
00:52:46,860 --> 00:52:50,050
We can have a press meeting and indoor event as planned

775
00:52:50,050 --> 00:52:53,140
and put the outdoor event on hold for now.

776
00:52:53,140 --> 00:52:55,140
What are you talking about?

777
00:52:55,140 --> 00:52:58,090
We have to make a spectacle for the unveiling.

778
00:52:58,090 --> 00:53:00,580
Don't you know people lose interest if you postpone?

779
00:53:00,580 --> 00:53:02,800
It's true, but there's even a heavy rain warning—

780
00:53:02,800 --> 00:53:05,920
I heard the contestants we invited are mostly in their 20s.

781
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:07,260
What's the point of being young?

782
00:53:07,260 --> 00:53:10,520
It's okay to get rained on a bit.

783
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:13,080
Let's just go as planned. Okay?

784
00:53:13,080 --> 00:53:15,300
Hand out raincoats to the audience.

785
00:53:15,300 --> 00:53:19,280
If there were any accidents, the chairman would be—

786
00:53:19,280 --> 00:53:20,830
Are you...

787
00:53:22,230 --> 00:53:24,810
ignoring what I said?

788
00:53:25,640 --> 00:53:27,960
Don't you know who I am?

789
00:53:27,960 --> 00:53:29,670
I'm the heir of this company.

790
00:53:29,670 --> 00:53:31,610
